<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1659,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1659,1684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from two geographically proximate localities in the Xe Kong drainage, a major subdrainage of the Mekong River in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[627,681,1696,1719]" name="Laos" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Laos</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[697,766,1695,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1939]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Map of the middle and lower Mekong with collection localities of A. bilustris; the symbol represents more than one locality." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203371/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[749,766,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1659,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,1732,1756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is the Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName box="[809,901,1732,1756]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Akysidae" genus="Akysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilustris">
<emphasis box="[809,901,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">bilustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “that lasts two lustra (i.e. ten years),” in reference to the fact that the specimens comprising the 
<typeStatus box="[802,850,1769,1793]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
series were collected in two expeditions exactly ten years apart.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
